# This file contains all the information to install several libraries in Visual Studio 2017

# Armadillo: library for using matrices in C++
In order to make Armadillo work on Visual Studio:
1-Once the project is open, select Property Manager > C/C++ > General > Additional Include Directories, and add armadillo "include" folder path;
2-In your project properties, go to Linker > General > Additional Library Directory, and add the path of the folders "AddS";
3-Add the names "liblapack.lib;libblas.lib" in Linker > Input > Additional Dependencies;
4-Compile application;
5-Once your application compiled correctly, copy the liblapack.dll and libblas.dll where your executable is ("Debug" folder inside the project).

